Intermediate Skateboarding

Advanced Tricks

Now that you've mastered the basics, it's time to dive into some advanced tricks to take your skateboarding to the next level:

  • Ollie: Learn how to pop the board off the ground and level it out in the air for a smooth ollie.
  • Kickflip: Practice flipping the board with your front foot while jumping to perform a kickflip.
  • Heelflip: Similar to a kickflip but flipping the board with your heel instead of your toe.
  • Pop Shove-It: Rotate the board 180 degrees while in the air without flipping it.
  • 50-50 Grind: Slide along a rail or ledge with both trucks grinding the surface.

Skatepark Etiquette

Skateparks can be crowded and chaotic, so it's important to follow proper etiquette to ensure everyone has a good time:

  • Wait Your Turn: Don't drop in on someone else's run; wait for them to finish before taking your turn.
  • Communicate: Signal your intentions to other skaters, whether you're dropping in or about to perform a trick.
  • Clean Up After Yourself: Pick up your trash and equipment to keep the skatepark clean for others to enjoy.
  • Respect the Rules: Obey any posted rules and regulations at the skatepark to ensure everyone's safety.

Skateboarding Gear

Having the right gear can make a big difference in your skateboarding experience:

  • Skateboard: Choose a deck size and shape that suits your style, along with quality trucks, wheels, and bearings.
  • Protective Gear: Invest in a helmet, knee pads, elbow pads, and wrist guards to prevent injuries.
  • Apparel: Wear comfortable clothing that allows for freedom of movement, along with skate shoes that provide grip and support.
  • Tools: Keep a skate tool handy for making adjustments to your board on the go.
